Key Match Events: Coby White made a go-ahead layup with 47 seconds left, giving the Bulls their first lead at 111-110.
Zach LaVine scored 35 points, 10 rebounds, and eight assists for Chicago.
Nikola Vucevic had 24 points and 11 rebounds, and Coby White finished with 23 points.
Post-Match Reflections: The Bulls won for the fourth time in five games, showing their recent strong performance.
The Spurs had a 19-point lead but couldn't maintain it as the Bulls mounted a comeback.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played at the United Center with a crowd of 18,886.
Both teams have upcoming games: Spurs vs. Milwaukee and Bulls vs. Indiana.
